The paper discusses cryptographic protocol analysis, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The use of Diffie-Hellman for key agreement involves mathematical concepts such as fields and cyclic groups, which are related to information theory (cs.IT) and computational complexity (cs.CC). The paper also discusses the implementation of the protocol analysis, which involves system modeling and verification (cs.SY) and logic in computer science (cs.LO).
